The Telegraph - Calcutta
 Wednesday, July 09, 2003  Good Morning Hello It's Wednesday, July 9, 2003				 																Roads to avoid				 																																	Lower Circular Road, between Camac Street and Lansdowne Road, due to work on the AJC Bose Road flyover. Buses and minibuses heading towards Alipore zoo will take the Lansdowne Road-Elgin Road-Ashutosh Mukherjee Road-Chowringhee-Queensway-Hospital Road-Lower Circular Road route. Those travelling towards Beckbagan will take the Ashutosh Mukherjee Road-Hazra Road-Ballygunge Phari-Syed Amir Ali Avenue route.				 																Concert				 																																	Drumscape featuring Bikram Ghosh on the tabla, S. Sekhar on the mridangam and Somnath Roy on the ghatam at British Council at 6.30 pm.				 																Accessories				 																																	Aakarshan 2003, a sale of artefacts, ceramics, glassware, kitchenware and other accessories, at Ice Skating Rink from 10 am to 8 pm.				 																Art watch				 																																	Hyperreality, an exhibition of rare contemporary Indian Art, at Gallery Caps from 11.30 am to 7.30 pm.				 																																	An exhibition of paintings by Suhas Roy at Galerie 88 from 11 am to 7 pm.
